# CLAUDE.md, agent orientation

This file is a local, uncommitted drop-in for a standard STS2 mod repo. Copy it to the
repo root and adjust the mod name. Keep it out of version control.

A person can do all of the tasks here without an agent. A person starts at README.md. The
documents for people are the primary record, and this file only points to them.

## What this is

This repo is a mod for Slay the Spire 2. It uses C# and Godot, with BaseLib and Harmony.
It follows the standard layout: `<Mod>Code/` for C#, `<Mod>/` for assets and
localization, `cards.csv` as the design sheet, `scripts/dev.sh` as the command hub.

The tools are in the [sts2-modding-mcp](https://github.com/sethmcleod/sts2-modding-mcp)
toolkit: the MCP server, the MCPTest game bridge on TCP 21337, GodotExplorer on 27020,
and the test engine. The general modding guides are in the toolkit
(`get_modding_guide`, start with the `dev_workflow` topic). The conventions for this mod
are in this repo. Do not assume sts2-modding-mcp is the only connected server.

## Commands

```sh
scripts/dev.sh publish      # build → import → publish → verify pck  (asset/loc changes)
scripts/dev.sh publish-fast # code-only changes (skips godot import)
scripts/dev.sh lint         # offline static three-way-rule check (no game)
scripts/dev.sh changelog    # draft CHANGELOG entries from commits since the last tag
scripts/dev.sh release <patch|minor|major|X.Y.Z>   # bump + roll changelog + package zip
scripts/dev.sh doctor       # ✓/✗ every prerequisite
```

Each change that a player can see needs an entry in `CHANGELOG.md` under
`## [Unreleased]`. `dotnet build` must pass with 0 errors; the localization analyzer runs
as part of the build.

## Rules you must not skip

- **Three-way update rule**: a card is in the code, the localization, and `cards.csv`. If
  you change one of the three, change all three. See CONTRIBUTING.md.
- **Design and code conventions**: see CONTRIBUTING.md.
- **The description code and the tooltip code must not read `Owner` without an
  `IsMutable` guard.** A canonical model (in the compendium) throws an exception.

## Live tests against the game (bridge)

The `testing` and `troubleshooting` guides in the toolkit list the hazards. The ones that
cost the most time:

- Use a **new game process** with a **spare save profile** (Profile 3 by convention).
  Never abandon a run during a combat; use the `die` console command instead.
- A custom entity needs the **full model id**, for example `card MYMOD-MY_CARD`. The
  short name does nothing, and it shows no error. Use the console command `dump` to find
  a model id.
- For the console commands `power` and `damage`, the target index `0` is the player and
  `1` is the first enemy: one more than the `target_index` of `play_card`.
- **Hot reload** (tier 2 and tier 3) works only from the main menu, and only **before the
  first combat** in the session.
- On macOS, a screen transition can stop while the game window does not have the focus.
